tabcli

Usage:
  tabcli [--json] <command> [options]

Commands:
  install
      Install the current-user Native Messaging manifest
  uninstall
      Remove product-managed current-user files
  status
      Show the active Chrome connection
  doctor
      Diagnose installation and connection without changes
  version
      Show product, Go, OS/CPU, and protocol versions
  tabs list [--window ID] [--group ID] [--ungrouped] [--inactive-for DURATION] [--sort FIELD] [--sort-order ORDER] [--include-activity]
      List current non-incognito Chrome tabs without changing Chrome state.
  groups list [--window ID]
      List current non-incognito Chrome tab groups without changing Chrome state.
  tabs content TAB_ID [--max-chars N]
      Get bounded visible text from one explicitly selected tab as privacy-sensitive untrusted data that may be sent to the configured model provider and is not persisted.
  tabs compare TAB_ID_A TAB_ID_B
      Compare the full visible text of exactly two selected tabs by SHA-256 without returning or persisting page text.
  tabs diff TAB_ID_A TAB_ID_B [--max-chars N] [--max-diff-chars N]
      Return only bounded changed visible-text lines for exactly two selected tabs; unchanged text and source snapshots are not returned or persisted.
  groups preview --plan FILE
      Validate a classification plan and preview its changes without modifying Chrome.
  groups apply --preview-id ID
      Apply one valid, user-approved preview.
  groups undo
      Undo the most recent successful bulk apply where possible.
  tabs close --confirm TAB_ID [TAB_ID ...]
      Close explicitly selected current Chrome tabs after user confirmation.
  mcp serve
      Serve the static tool catalog over stdio
